{"key":"processedPost-9580229","value":{"id":9580229,"first":9580191,"last":9581692,"when":1231566082,"utime":"01/10/09 07:41 AM","content":"You can't <i>pasteurize</i> in a microwave.&nbsp; All you can do is superheat the material.&nbsp; You'll have more success if you'll mix all your ingredients, moisturize to field capacity, and then heat until the center of the substrate is at 140F to 160F for one hour.&nbsp; If you can pull that off in a microwave, go for it, but there's far easier and better ways to pasteurize.<br />RR","title":"Re: gypsum coir ver microwave pasturizing for Subtrate","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}